flowchart TB
    accTitle: Homelab 3-2-1 recovery architecture
    accDescr: Live data on the server and RAID10 NAS feeds verified local database dumps, a weekly server mirror, and Btrfs snapshots. Selected Immich originals and a verified database dump are encrypted by Restic and stored off-site in Backblaze B2.

    subgraph PRIMARY[" "]
        direction TB
        PRIMARY_LABEL["PRIMARY SYSTEMS · HOME"]:::layer
        SERVER["Server SSD\ncontainers · code · runtime state"]:::primary
        NAS["Btrfs RAID10 NAS\n4 × 4 TB · NFS application data"]:::primary
        PRIMARY_LABEL ~~~ SERVER
        SERVER --> NAS
    end

    subgraph LOCAL[" "]
        direction TB
        LOCAL_LABEL["LOCAL RECOVERY · SAME SITE"]:::layer
        DUMPS["NAS-local verified DB dumps\n+ portable volume archives"]:::local
        MIRROR["NAS-local weekly server mirror\n+ manifest + inventory"]:::local
        SNAPS["Read-only Btrfs snapshots\n7 daily · 4 weekly · monthly"]:::local
        LOCAL_LABEL ~~~ DUMPS
    end

    subgraph OFFSITE[" "]
        direction TB
        OFFSITE_LABEL["OFF-SITE · SEPARATE FAILURE DOMAIN"]:::layer
        RESTIC["Restic\nselected originals + verified dump\nclient-side encryption"]:::offsite
        B2["Backblaze B2\nEU object storage"]:::offsite
        OFFSITE_LABEL ~~~ RESTIC
        RESTIC --> B2
    end

    SERVER --> DUMPS
    SERVER --> MIRROR
    NAS --> SNAPS
    NAS --> RESTIC
    DUMPS --> RESTIC

